any sense of it.

496
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:09,090
But the important
thing is, the only way

497
00:20:09,090 --> 00:20:13,500
to confirm that you're allowed
to connect to this instance

498
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,660
is that the public
password basically

499
00:20:15,660 --> 00:20:17,527
has an unlocking password.

500
00:20:17,527 --> 00:20:19,860
This private password comes
in and says, OK, well, now I

501
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:21,007
put these two together.

502
00:20:21,007 --> 00:20:22,590
Now, all of a sudden,
I know that this

503
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:23,910
is a secure connection.

504
00:20:23,910 --> 00:20:26,760
This is the only password,
the only private password that

505
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:28,090
works with this public one.

506
00:20:28,090 --> 00:20:29,838
So anybody can see
this public one.

507
00:20:29,838 --> 00:20:31,380
We come in with our
private password.

508
00:20:31,380 --> 00:20:33,380
And all of a sudden, it
says, oh, actually, this

509
00:20:33,380 --> 00:20:34,570
is a trusted entity.

510
00:20:34,570 --> 00:20:36,180
So it's really
important that when

511
00:20:36,180 --> 00:20:38,820
you have this secure
key pair or you

512
00:20:38,820 --> 00:20:41,520
create this key pairs is
that you keep track of these,

513
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:44,190
that they're going to be
kept secure on your device

514
00:20:44,190 --> 00:20:48,100
or separate from
any other users.

515
00:20:48,100 --> 00:20:50,380
Once you have created one
