689
00:27:58,670 --> 00:28:00,630
I can attach them to
different computers.

690
00:28:00,630 --> 00:28:03,840
So I can create this
external hard drive

691
00:28:03,840 --> 00:28:05,580
for this EC2 instance.

692
00:28:05,580 --> 00:28:07,590
I can terminate
this EC2 instance

693
00:28:07,590 --> 00:28:11,450
but keep my EBS volume alive,
and plug it into a new computer.

694
00:28:11,450 --> 00:28:13,200
So I can plug it into
a new EC2 instance,

695
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:15,170
if I need to use it again.

696
00:28:15,170 --> 00:28:18,060
It is important to note
that these are charged.

697
00:28:18,060 --> 00:28:20,340
So you will pay for EBS volumes.

698
00:28:20,340 --> 00:28:22,090
So when you terminate
the instance,

699
00:28:22,090 --> 00:28:24,690
if you've created it in this
way where you create the EBS

700
00:28:24,690 --> 00:28:27,852
storage, the volume with
