711
00:28:49,712 --> 00:28:50,920
You will be charged for that.

712
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:53,587
So you won't be paying for your
EC2 instance while it's stopped,

713
00:28:53,587 --> 00:28:55,620
but you will pay
for your EBS volume.

714
00:28:55,620 --> 00:28:58,655
The pricing on these,
I believe, right now--

715
00:28:58,655 --> 00:28:59,280
don't quote me.

716
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,840
Let's see.

717
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:02,200
EBS volume pricing.

718
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:09,690
I believe it's like $0.30,
like $0.30 a gigabyte.

719
00:29:09,690 --> 00:29:10,357
GP2.

720
00:29:10,357 --> 00:29:11,940
I think we're looking
at a GP2 volume.

721
00:29:11,940 --> 00:29:12,605
Yeah, GP2.

722
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:21,220
Typically, at $0.10
per gigabyte month.

723
00:29:21,220 --> 00:29:25,050
So for each gigabyte you
have live for a month,

724
00:29:25,050 --> 00:29:28,110
you will be charged $0.10
per those gigabytes.

725
00:29:28,110 --> 00:29:31,820
So for example here, if we left
this one live-- now granted

726
00:29:31,820 --> 00:29:34,012
this is free-tier eligible.

727
00:29:34,012 --> 00:29:35,970
So if you're still within
your first 12 months,

728
00:29:35,970 --> 00:29:37,910
you get up to 30
